AGI&nbsp; -&nbsp;The US Senate approved a $95 billion aid package for Ukraine, Israel and Taiwan. Of these 61 billion dollars will go to Ukraine, with President Joe Biden who promised that new weapons supplies will be delivered quickly to the war zone to counter the Russian advance; 26,4 to Israel and 8.1 to the Indo-Pacific.
&nbsp;
The law now passes to President Joe Biden's signature. Its passage is a significant victory for the President of the United States, for the Democrats of Congress and for the Republican Party leader in the Senate Mitch McConnell, who has long pushed for the sending of aid to Ukraine, although the right wing of his party has increasingly split on support in Kiev.
&nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky, America leader of the free world</h2>
"I am grateful to the United States Senate for today approving vital aid to Ukraine. I thank the majority leader Chuck Schumer and Republican leader Mitch McConnell for their strong leadership in carrying out this bipartisan legislation, as well as all US senators who voted in favour." So in a post on X, the president of Ukraine, Volodymyr&nbsp;Zelensky thanked the U.S. for approving an aid package of 61 billion.
&nbsp;
"This vote strengthens America's role as a forum for democracy and free world leaders. - he added - I am also grateful to all Americans who continue to support Ukraine and recognize that the historical significance of this bill goes beyond politics. I also appreciate the support of President Biden and I look forward to the draft law being signed soon and that the next military aid package corresponds to the resolve I always see in our negotiations. Ukraine's long-range capabilities, artillery and air defense are key tools to quickly restore peace."
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Biden, weapons to Ukraine this week
"I will fix this bill and address myself to the American people as soon as they arrive on my desk tomorrow, so we can start sending weapons and equipment to Ukraine this week," Biden said, adding that the approval of the bill shows that America is "resolutely in favor of Ukraine". democracy and freedom, and against tyranny and oppression."
&nbsp;

